title: NDFD, NOAA, Calmer seas near Deepwater Horizon site in the GOM, USA, July 10, 2010
name: NDFD, NOAA, Calmer seas near Deepwater Horizon site in the GOM, USA, July 10, 2010
description:
The poly shapefile shows significant wave height data for portions of coastal waters in the GOM.

The data was extracted from NDFD's extraction program and then converted to shapefile. The NDFD wave height predictions are valid between 10:00 on 10th 11:59 UTC on 13th.

Note that compared to July 7, the seas are much calmer in the vicinity of Deep Water Horizon, predicted wave heights will not exceed 2 feet. BP is undertaking a major operation to
replace the contaiment cap, claiming this will help them collect between 50,000 to 80,000 barrels of oil/gas per day. 
The significant wave activity has shifted westward towards Texas coastal waters and to some extent near Florida coast.

Look elsewhere on Finder! for wave data over the next several days. Use key word "Wave height".
